ZH: 我昨天晚上做了一个关于妖怪的梦。
EN: I dreamt about a ghost last night.

ZH: 传说中妖怪会在月圆之夜出现。
EN: It is said that ghosts appear on the night of a full moon.

ZH: 那个故事讲了一只妖怪如何变成了一只猫。
EN: The story tells how a ghost transformed into a cat.

ZH: 夜里的森林里有很多奇怪的妖怪。
EN: There are many strange monsters in the forest at night.

ZH: 小孩子害怕在晚上看到妖怪。
EN: Children are afraid of seeing ghosts at night.

ZH: 我们听到了一个妖怪的尖叫声从远处传来。
EN: We heard a ghostly scream coming from a distance.

ZH: 传说中的妖怪总是喜欢吃人的心脏。
EN: Legends say that ghosts always crave human hearts.

ZH: 我看到一个妖怪在月光下飞翔。
EN: I saw a ghost flying under the moonlight.

ZH: 妖怪出现的时候，天空会变得阴暗。
EN: When ghosts appear, the sky becomes gloomy.

ZH: 在我的梦里，我变成了一个妖怪。
EN: In my dream, I turned into a ghost.

ZH: 这是一个关于日本妖怪的电影。
EN: This movie is about Japanese ghosts.

ZH: 有人说这个房子里闹鬼了，有妖怪出现。
EN: Some say this house is haunted, with ghosts appearing.

ZH: 我可以保护你不被妖怪伤害。
EN: I can protect you from being harmed by ghosts.

ZH: 这是一本关于中国妖怪传说的书。
EN: This is a book about Chinese ghost legends.

ZH: 那个小村庄里有一个被封印住的妖怪。
EN: There is a sealed monster in that small village.

ZH: 妖怪在黑暗中隐藏，等待时机袭击。
EN: Ghosts lurk in the dark, waiting for the right moment to strike.

ZH: 他的外表看起来像妖怪一样，但他的内心是善良的。
EN: He looks like a ghost on the outside, but his heart is kind.

ZH: 我们打败了那只凶恶的妖怪。
EN: We defeated the evil ghost.

ZH: 据说妖怪会喜欢吃小孩的心灵。
EN: It is said that ghosts enjoy devouring the souls of children.

ZH: 如果你相信妖怪的存在，你会更害怕夜晚。
EN: If you believe in the existence of ghosts, you will be more afraid of the night.
